President Obama has declared a major disaster in the State of Texas due to severe storms, tornadoes, and flooding. Federal aid will be provided to supplement state and local recovery efforts. Assistance will be available to affected individuals in the counties of Jasper, Newton, and Orange, including grants for temporary housing, home repairs, and low-cost loans for uninsured property losses. Federal funding will also be available for emergency work and hazard mitigation measures statewide. The Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected area has been named. Damage surveys are ongoing, and more counties and forms of assistance may be designated in the future. Residents and business owners can apply for assistance online or by phone. For further information, contact the FEMA news desk.